title: EastEnders fans worried for Dot Branning after car crash cliffhanger leaves her fate in the balance
text:
EastEnders fans worried for Dot Branning after car crash cliffhanger leaves her fate in the balance The Walford favourite was involved in a terrifying end to Thursday night's episode Share Comments By Alistair McGeorge 20:21, 23 FEB 2017 Updated 20:23, 23 FEB 2017 TV Video Loading Video Unavailable Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now Watch this video again Video will play in Dot Cotton in car crash horror on Eastenders Share this video Watch Next soaps EastEnders fans are concerned for Dot Branning after a cliffhanger ending that saw her driving into oncoming traffic.
In terrifying scenes at the conclusion to Thursday night's episode, the character - whose eyesight has been worrying her more recently - was using Jack's sat nav to help her drive grandson Matthew to the local garden centre.
However, the electronic voice began giving faulty instructions, and Dot was seen panicking as her confidence behind the wheel disappeared - but it wasn't over.
Dot's confidence went behind the wheel (Photo: BBC) She ended up facing the traffic (Photo: BBC) In the closing moments, viewers saw her miss a 'no entry sign' and head towards oncoming traffic.
Read More EastEnders spoiler: Denise forced to deal with the consequences of her actions She swerved off the round and into a verge - but her health was unknown as the credits rolled.
One viewer said: "On behalf of everybody, LEAVE DOT ALONE!! @bbceastenders #eastenders"
Her eyesight has been concerning her (Photo: BBC) Will she be ok? (Photo: BBC) While another added: "Omg Dot please be okay #EastEnders"
However, other viewers were more amused by the scene, and commented on the green screen used to film it.
"Poor old Dot Cotton should never have been allowed behind the wheel of a stationary car in front of a green screen," quipped one fan.
Another joked: "Dot is actually played by Andy Serkis in front of a s**t green screen."
